# iOS Architecture & Code Quality Standards

## Architecture & Layers

- Enforce a clear layer boundary: `UI → ViewModel → UseCase/Service → Repository → API/Storage`
- Views present data only; view models handle UI logic; services handle networking and persistence
- Prefer composition + protocols over inheritance; no new singletons — use dependency injection
- State must be single-source-of-truth per feature; never duplicate the same state across layers
- Separate models and mappers for API vs domain vs UI representations

## Swift & SwiftUI Code Quality

- Use clear, descriptive names that reflect domain concepts
- No force unwraps (`!`) or forced casts; prefer `guard` + early returns for optional handling
- Split long functions or complex `body` implementations into smaller, focused units
- Minimize logic in SwiftUI `body`; move it to computed properties or view models
- Break large views into smaller subviews to aid compiler performance and readability
- Use property wrappers (`@State`, `@Binding`, `@Observable`, `@Environment`, etc.) intentionally
- Keep UI updates on the main actor; make async effects and navigation explicit

## Accessibility

- Use semantic SwiftUI components with meaningful labels, hints, and traits
- Ensure dynamic type compatibility and sufficient color contrast
